Interesting fact is that during the 1905 Russian-Japanese war, Saint Nicholas was the only ethnic Russian in Japan.

As a strong patriot, he prayed for Russian victory daily, but he ordered the Japanese Orthodox faithful to pray for the Emperor and for Japan to win instead.

St. Nicholas often went to buddhist or shinto/pagan temples and studied their faith actively.

When the Emperor wanted to celebrate his anniversary, the saint agreed to a big public fest, not out of pride, but because he knew this can attract many to Christianity. Very curious.
